"n.礼让，礼仪 【英】 n.礼让,礼仪(courtes y; civility) n. 礼貌, 礼仪 = courtesy = civility 【记】com共同, it他, y外国人: 共同向他们外国人学习, 因为他们很有礼貌. 【反】enmity(n 敌意; 憎恨) 【记】community，生活在社区，人们都需讲礼仪； com MIT，来到MIT，人们都很讲礼仪，文明 【相关】amity 友好, 亲善关系 comity (n.)  early 15c., ""association,"" from French comité, from Latin comitas ""courtesy, friendliness, kindness, affability,"" from comis ""courteous, friendly, kind,"" of uncertain origin. Meaning ""courtesy"" in English is from 1540s. Phrase comity of nations attested from 1862: ""The obligation recognized by civilized nations to respect each other's laws and usages as far as their separate interests allow."""
